cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on deep learning and the attacks on the initial weights of a network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the security aspect of deep learning, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper uses the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the efficacy of the attacks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
